Tyskl. 12-13, 20, 22, 28 o. 38, Danm. 19, Ital. 21, Norge 26, 33 o. 38, Frankr. 27 o. 31, Holk 27, Belg. 31, Engl. o. Skottl. 35, Sovjet 36, Finl. 39. Lär i Hedemora 14-16, e. lär. i Eskilstuna 17-19, adj. i Sala 19, i Gäv’le 24-37, adj. i modersm,. o. tyska v. Halmstads h. a. 1. sed. 37. Skr.: Metoder v. d!en första grammmnd:-visn. i tyska (Berätt. över 25. sv. lärov :lär :mö’tet).
translated: Högbom, Sigurd Emanuel, high school teacher, Halmstad, born June 19th, 1890 in Piteå to senior rector M.G.H. and Theresia Norrbom. Married in 1928 to Emmy Nyman. Completed high school in Umeå in 1909, obtained a master's degree in Uppsala in 1913. Traveled to Germany in 1912-13, 1920, 1922, 1928, and 1938; Denmark in 1919; Italy in 1921; Norway in 1926, 1933, and 1938; France in 1927 and 1931; Holland in 1927; Belgium in 1931; England and Scotland in 1935; Soviet Union in 1936; and Finland in 1939. Taught in Hedemora from 1914-1916, as a substitute teacher in Eskilstuna from 1917-1919, high school teacher in Sala in 1919, in Gävle from 1924-1937, and as a high school teacher in mother tongue and German at Halmstad high school since 1937. Author of Methods for the First German Grammar Demonstration (Report on the 25th Swedish Gymnasium Teachers' Meeting).
